{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784071483471705002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"immoveable-tanned-snail","assignee":"joeoakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"HMAC-SHA256","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","head_sha":"b5f4c9e3730067e719a4f4a1ca0d6ca5625b62da","key_id":"412fa5372ad877e0","kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 7c84-40dc-c112-410c","material: ce4af333a8d00138","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 12","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (b5f4c9e37)","regver: 8952be2f5b88eba7","verified-at-sha:9edb0cdc31d21c9c2ccd1730065225978f258573","dep ed13f74604708c18b2839eb14d368316bae98b9bcbfd7fd930c7f0ea3578a783 src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py"],"signature":"ceede7572c43fa3e18a1789ffb7424812846beba7e0e8a00f35b822dbac9ba96","signed_at":1784071392436638000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":0,"unsigned":7},"authorship_ledger":[],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-209_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"90514dff-8b46-4f42-ae53-a1e35fc50ef6","comments":[],"created_at":1784067234905044001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"2ce573ca-4813-4193-b2d5-6ad187be11f3","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"4e19-5846-0e3f-4882"}],"description":"## Why\n\nThe code-review `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar (`code_review_result_v1`) persists only the SURFACED\nfindings тАФ the `blocking`, `advisory`, and `coaching` buckets тАФ and omits the `dropped` and\n`indeterminate` findings that Pass-3 produced. It also does not persist the numeric\n`block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` each finding was judged against. So \"the complete Pass-1\nfinding list\" is not recoverable for a code review, unlike plan review.\n\n## Dependency\n\nThis story **depends on 4e19** (plan-review lossless v2), which lands first in the stack and makes\nthe SHARED review kernel stamp the resolved boundary on every decided finding: `pass3_decide`\nreturns `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` and `pass3_over_findings` merges them, so every\ncode-review finding (via `code_review_decide`) already carries them by the time this story runs.\n4e19 also adds those two fields (plus `evidence`/`scenarios`) to the plan-review `_slim`, so the two\nsidecars **converge** in shape тАФ this story does not introduce a field plan-review lacks.\n\n## What\n\nExtend the code-review sidecar to `code_review_result_v2`, pooling the four buckets the code-review\ngate actually produces тАФ `blocking`, `advisory` (surfaced), `dropped`, `indeterminate` тАФ with each\nfinding's full Pass-2 `verification` and Pass-3 determination (`decision`/`priority`/тАж), plus the\nresolved `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` (stamped by the 4e19 kernel change). There is **no\n`overflow` bucket** in code review: unlike plan-review (which applies an advisory cap that spills to\n`overflow`), `code_review_decide` partitions only into `{blocking, surfaced, dropped, indeterminate}`\nand the code-review verdict schema has no `overflow` property.\n\n## Scope\n\nThe `dropped`/`indeterminate` buckets are computed by `code_review_decide` but are **not** currently\nforwarded to the terminal verdict тАФ `code_review_coach` assembles only\n`{verdict, blocking, advisory, coaching, coverage}`, and `apply_region_gated_floor` only appends its\nown novelty-floor drops post-hoc. So the wiring must be extended:\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/code-review.yaml` тАФ in the `verdict` step's `with:` block, pass\n  `dropped: ${{ steps.decide.outputs.dropped }}` and\n  `indeterminate: ${{ steps.decide.outputs.indeterminate }}` (alongside the existing `blocking`\n  and `surfaced`).\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py` тАФ `code_review_coach` accepts `dropped`/\n  `indeterminate` inputs and includes them in its returned verdict dict; update its\n  `code_review_coach_input`/`_output` schemas to allow the two new (optional) arrays.\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py` тАФ bump `SCHEMA` to `code_review_result_v2`; in\n  `build_payload`, add `dropped`/`indeterminate` (norm-id-stamped, like `blocking`/`advisory`), each\n  finding retaining its `verification`/`decision`/`block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled`; KEEP the\n  separate `blocking`/`advisory` lists (so the surfaced reader is unchanged) and the change metadata\n  (`change_id`/`revision`/`change_fingerprint`) + `deps`. `_latest_payload_with_ts` and\n  `latest_code_review_result` accept BOTH `code_review_result_v1` and `_v2` (replace the\n  `== SCHEMA` guard with membership in `{v1, v2}`), so old records still read and the surfaced\n  reader keeps returning the `blocking + advisory` union.\n\nCode-review findings carry no `evidence`/`scenarios` (those are plan-review Pass-1 fields); this\nstory does not persist them for code review.\n\n## Enumerated consumers to update\n\n- `tests/unit/test_code_review_ws4.py:210` asserts `payload[\"schema\"] == \"code_review_result_v1\"`\n  on a fresh emit; update it to `_v2` (the schema bumped).\n- `docs/experiments/derive_code_review_threshold.py` is a jq/offline consumer that filters on\n  `code_review_result_v1`; note that it should accept `_v2` too (or is left as historical тАФ out of\n  this story's code scope, flagged for the reader).\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\n`v1` code-review sidecars remain readable (new buckets absent тЖТ default to `[]`). The novelty-floor\nreader that consumes surfaced findings keeps returning the `blocking + advisory` union, so\nregion-gating is unaffected. No backfill. Reverting bumps `SCHEMA` back to `v1` and stops writing the\n`dropped`/`indeterminate` buckets; already-written `v2` records stay readable because the reader\nstill accepts both schemas (the reader change is independently safe to keep).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `build_payload` produces a `code_review_result_v2` payload that pools `blocking`, `advisory`,\n      `dropped`, and `indeterminate`, each finding retaining its `verification`, Pass-3 `decision`,\n      and resolved `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` plus a `norm_id`. Oracle: a unit test driving\n      `build_payload` with a verdict containing all four buckets and asserting on the payload JSON.\n- [ ] `code_review_coach` forwards `dropped`/`indeterminate` from the decide step into the terminal\n      verdict dict. Oracle: a contract test calling the `code_review_coach` op with those inputs and\n      asserting they appear in the returned verdict.\n- [ ] `latest_code_review_result` reads both a `v1` and a `v2` code-review sidecar. Oracle: a unit\n      test with one hand-written record of each schema.\n- [ ] The novelty-floor surfaced-findings reader returns exactly the `blocking + advisory` union\n      from a `v2` payload, unchanged vs an equivalent `v1` payload. Oracle: a unit test comparing the\n      two.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py","reason":"pool all buckets + thresholds into v2 payload"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","4e19-5846-0e3f-4882"],["parent","ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6"]],"parent_id":"ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","parent_status_uuid":"6143835e-ae6c-4a92-a543-0ca41069b01a","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"7c84-40dc-c112-410c","ticket_type":"story","title":"code-review sidecar -> lossless v2 (all buckets + thresholds)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e7b12717-ffa5-414d-9c6c-45269a1d2c84","d86dfa49-5194-4ac2-bed5-e5fe6d7b3f2e","2ce573ca-4813-4193-b2d5-6ad187be11f3","5bf9a98e-9097-4a44-bba6-a4eeb180828a","10a776a3-c1ba-4386-ba1d-5f7593b8c8c6","6143835e-ae6c-4a92-a543-0ca41069b01a","ce581b18-6ffc-4eba-ae55-5aeb88cfa669"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784071483471705002,"uuid":"69da6ba4-0d31-4a89-8dce-75646220cbc5"}